# Next.js & React Standards (Dread.lol)

Repo-specific: run **`npm run ci`** before merge (see `CONTRIBUTING.md`). Paths use **`app/`** and **`lib/`** (no `src/` root).

## React & TypeScript

- Use **function declarations** for components. Avoid `React.FC` / `React.FunctionComponent` unless a generic component requires it.
- Prefer **named exports** for components; default exports only where the framework requires (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, etc.).
- **Never** use `any`. Prefer `unknown` plus narrowing, or proper generics.
- Prefer **explicit return types** on exported functions and public APIs.
- Avoid **enum** — use string unions or `as const` objects.
- **Never** use array index as React `key` when the list can reorder; use stable IDs.
- **Controlled inputs** — avoid mixing controlled and uncontrolled for the same field.
- **Effects** — do not use `useEffect` for data that can be fetched on the server or derived during render.

### Default props and referential stability

```tsx
// ❌ New array default each render can break memoized children
function List({ items = [] }: Props) {}

// ✅ Stable default — module-level constant or useMemo when derived
const DEFAULT_ITEMS: Item[] = [];
function List({ items = DEFAULT_ITEMS }: Props) {}
```

- Avoid **prop drilling** beyond ~2 levels; prefer composition, context, or a small client store when needed.

## Next.js App Router

- Default to **Server Components**. Add `'use client'` only for interactivity, browser APIs, or hooks.
- Push **`'use client'`** boundaries as deep as reasonable — maximize RSC coverage.
- Do not **`fetch` in Client Components** when a parent Server Component can fetch and pass props.
- Use **`next/image`** for images; avoid raw `<img>` for app content.
- Use **`next/link`** for internal navigation; avoid `<a href>` for in-app routes.
- Implement **`generateMetadata`** for every `page.tsx` that should be publicly indexed.
- Set **route segment config** (`dynamic`, `revalidate`, etc.) explicitly when behavior matters — do not rely only on implicit caching.
- **Parallel / intercepting routes** — add a short comment explaining routing intent.
- **`loading.tsx` and `error.tsx`** — add for route segments that do async work where UX needs them (align with existing app patterns).

## Data fetching

- Server Components may fetch directly — no API route as a middleman for data the app owns.
- Use `fetch` with explicit **`cache` / `next.revalidate`** (or document why defaults are intentional).
- Prefer **Server Actions** for mutations (forms → actions) unless streaming or UX requires client `fetch`.
- Never expose **DB clients, queries, or secrets** to Client Components.
- Validate external input at boundaries with **`zod`**; centralize shared schemas (e.g. `lib/api-schemas.ts` or colocated modules) and reuse.
- **`route.ts`** — webhooks, third-party callbacks, and intentional public APIs; not for routine internal server → client data that RSC can carry.

## State management

- Prefer **URL state** (search params) for shareable UI state.
- Prefer **Server Component props** for server-originated data.
- **`useState` / `useReducer`** for local ephemeral UI.
- **React Context** — low-frequency global state (theme, auth snapshot, locale). Avoid high-frequency updates in Context.
- Complex client global state — small dedicated libraries only if needed; avoid Redux unless already standard here.
- **No stored derived state** — compute from source during render.

## Hooks

- Custom hooks: name **`use*`**; colocate under the feature (e.g. `app/.../useFeature.ts`) or **`lib/`** when shared.
- Data-fetching hooks must handle **loading, error, and empty** states.
- Keep **domain/business logic** out of presentational components when it obscures testing — extract hooks or `lib/` helpers.
- **`useEffect`**: always include a dependency array; add cleanup for subscriptions, timers, and listeners; prefer **`useSyncExternalStore`** for external store sync; do not use effects purely to derive state you can compute in render.

## Styling

- **Tailwind CSS** is primary; avoid ad-hoc CSS except globals / tokens (this repo uses Tailwind v4 — follow existing `app` CSS patterns).
- Prefer **conditional classes** via a small helper or consistent patterns; if you introduce **`cn()`** (clsx + tailwind-merge), use it instead of string concatenation.
- Avoid **`style={{}}`** when Tailwind can express the same.
- **Design tokens** — centralize (e.g. theme CSS variables / shared classes); avoid one-off magic numbers where tokens exist.
- **Variants** — prefer a single pattern (e.g. CVA) if the codebase adopts it; avoid many boolean style props.
- **Dark mode** — Tailwind `dark:` + class strategy; avoid JS-driven style toggles except for `class` on `html`/`body`.

## Error handling

- No empty **`catch`** blocks.
- **Server Actions and `route.ts`**: wrap async work in try/catch; return typed error shapes consistently.
- Consider **`Result`-style** handling for domain failures where it clarifies control flow.
- Use **`error.tsx`** for route errors; client **`ErrorBoundary`** for isolated UI failures.
- Log server-side with **request/user context**; never log secrets or full raw PII.
- User-facing errors: **clear and safe**; internal details stay server-side.

## API design (`route.ts`)

- End-to-end typing; validate bodies and query params with **`zod`**.
- Consistent shapes: e.g. `{ data: T }` vs `{ error: { message, code } }` — match existing API patterns in the repo.
- Correct **HTTP status codes** (400 client, 401/403 auth, 404, 500 server).
- **Authenticate and authorize** before business logic on protected routes.
- **Rate-limit** public or abuse-prone endpoints where applicable.

## Authentication and security

- No JWTs in **`localStorage`** — sessions via **httpOnly** cookies (this app uses server-side sessions).
- Secrets only in **environment variables**; never commit `.env` files.
- Validate and sanitize **server-side**; never trust client-only checks for security.
- **Server Actions** that mutate protected data must verify the session / authorization first.
- **Security headers** — configure in Next config as needed (`CSP`, `X-Frame-Options`, etc.).
- **Parameterized queries** only — never concatenate untrusted input into queries.

## Performance

- Periodically check bundle size (e.g. analyzer in CI or locally) before large client additions.
- **`next/dynamic`** for heavy client-only chunks not needed on first paint.
- **`next/image`**: explicit dimensions or `fill` + positioned parent to limit CLS.
- **`React.memo` / `useMemo` / `useCallback`** — use when profiling shows benefit or stable references are required for children; avoid blanket memoization.
- Long lists — virtualize when needed (e.g. **@tanstack/virtual**).

## Testing

- **Vitest** — unit tests for pure logic and hooks.
- **React Testing Library** — components: behavior and a11y, not implementation details.
- **Playwright** — `test:e2e` for critical flows (`*.spec.ts` under e2e conventions).
- Prefer **MSW** at the network boundary over deep module mocks when feasible.
- Avoid **snapshot-only** UI tests as the primary guard.

## CI (this repo)

Before merge, **`npm run ci`** must pass: typecheck, ESLint, Stylelint, TSQLLint, CSSLint, JSHint (see `CONTRIBUTING.md`), Vitest, i18n check. Run **`npm run build`** when changing imports, RSC boundaries, or routing.
